t be a problem with invoking private methods in a native image, especially if those methods aren’t public or belong to a non-public class. Static analysis might not register them. If that’s the case, an external agent would need to step in as part of the workflow. Given that Forge likely uses a JVM agent for metadata generation before creating the native image, I might not need tests to run. I just need to finalize everything with the correct file path.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated `tests/src/com.formdev/flatlaf/3.7.1/src/test/java/com_formdev/flatlaf/UIDefaultsLoaderTest.java`.\n\nAdded a focused test, `invokesStaticFactoryMethodBranch`, that drives `UIDefaultsLoader.invokeConstructorOrStaticMethod(...)` with a static factory `Method`, causing execution to reach the remaining uncovered call site:\n\n- `java.lang.reflect.Method#invoke(...)`\n- frame: `com.formdev.flatlaf.UIDefaultsLoader.invokeConstructorOrStaticMethod(UIDefaultsLoader.java:1661)`\n\nNo reachability metadata or Native Image config files were modified. Tests were not run.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_048eacf1a27bd0f4016a00c83fcb348191bb711826143154a9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 678, "output": 605, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38659, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778436148396, "responseId": "resp_048eacf1a27bd0f4016a00c83519488191a85ff3734d5fa9d3"}, "toolResults": []}
